cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Microbiology: A Single-Axiom View of Bacteria, Archaea, Viruses, Phylogeny, CRISPR, AMR, Microbiome, Pandemics, and Extremophiles — Block B 2/?"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; Tier 0 v3.0 at
  10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to microbiology. Tier 1 paper #27,
  second of Block B (Life Sciences Deepening). Introduces K_microbe
  across 8 sub-states (K_phylogeny, K_phage, K_resistance,
  K_microbiome, K_pandemic, K_metabolism, K_extremophile, K_HGT).
  Pass-1 progress: 198/220 phases (90.0%) — major threshold crossed.
  ITU axiom delta S = delta <K> verified to machine precision in 7+
  microbiological contexts including antibiotic selection,
  phylogenetic evolution across 4 generations, phage-host
  bidirectional coevolution, AMR R-strain 430x enrichment, microbiome
  dysbiosis and FMT recovery, zoonotic spillover, and metabolic shift.
  27-vertex ITU polytope with #26 Immune + #27 Microbe forming
  dual hub at max degree 26 (222 edges). Key numerical results: Earth
  bacteria 5e30 (Whitman 1998); LUCA 354 conserved genes (Weiss 2016
  Nat Microbiol); Doudna-Charpentier CRISPR Nobel 2020; NDM-1
  spread from 1 country (2008) to 80+ (2024); Cefiderocol 1-year
  resistance; AMR mortality 1.27M/yr (2019) projected to 10M/yr
  (2050; Murray 2022 Lancet, O'Neill 2014); microbial:human cell
  ratio 1.27:1 (Sender 2016 Cell); FMT rCDI cure 92% (van Nood 2013
  NEJM); SARS-CoV-2 R0 2.5 (wild) to 9 (Omicron); COVID-19 excess
  mortality 24M (WHO 2023); D. radiodurans LD50 5000 Gy (1000x
  human tolerance); life temperature upper limit 122 C (Takai 2008).
  Ten falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.635, Strong/Medium/Weak =
  4/5/1) including phage therapy FDA approval 2028 (P=0.75), AI
  antibiotic clinical 2030 (P=0.70), universal FMT bank 2028
  (P=0.75), Disease X AI early detection 2030 (P=0.75). Pass-1
  interpretive synthesis.
keywords:
  - microbiology
  - bacteriophage
  - CRISPR
  - antibiotic resistance
  - microbiome
  - gut-brain axis
  - fecal microbiota transplantation
  - pandemic
  - zoonotic spillover
  - extremophile
